text.p: The U.S. Treasury said its Dutch auction of $18.28 billion of 2-yr notes produced a high yield of 5.930 percent and said it awarded 56 percent of bids at the high.
The interest rate on the notes will be 5-7/8 percent.
The median yield was 5.920 percent and the low yield was 5.890 percent.
A total of $47.890 billion in bids was received. Treasury said it received $1.01 billion in noncompetitive bids.
The bid to cover ratio was 2.62. The bills will be issued Oct 31 and mature Oct 31, 1998.
The high yield was down from the 6.080 at the last auction of 2-yr notes on Sept 25 and was the lowest since 5.235 percent on Feb 27.
